'''Nasser Essa Shafi Al-Shardan Al-Dawsari''' ({{langx|ar|ناصر عيسى الدوسري}}; born 19 December 1998) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]], [[Defensive Midfielder|defensive-midfielder]] or [[Central Midfielder|central-midfielder]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]] and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|nasser-al-dawsari/465476}}</ref>

==Club career==
Al-Dawsari started his career at Al-Hilal in 2011 at the age of 13. 23 November 2021, Al-Dawsari scored the fastest goal ever in the [[AFC Champions League]], just 16 seconds into the game, propelling his side to a 2–0 victory over [[Pohang Steelers]] to secure a record fourth continental title for [[Al-Hilal FC|Al Hilal]].<ref name=AFCgoal />

